=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Cyclize dimethyl 2-aminoterephthalate with formamidine acetate (or HC(OEt)3/NH3) to give methyl 7-carboxylate quinazolin-4(3H)-one (the anthranilate ester forms the 4-oxo quinazoline, the second ester remains as CO2Me) | Step 2: Treat this quinazolinone with POCl3 to form methyl 4-chloroquinazoline-7-carboxylate | Step 3: N3-alkylate with tert-butyl (3-bromopropyl)carbamate (BocNH(CH2)3Br), base, to give methyl 3-(3-Boc-aminopropyl)-4-chloroquinazoline-7-carboxylate | Step 4: Displace the 4-chloro group with 3,4,5-trimethoxyaniline to obtain methyl 3-(3-Boc-aminopropyl)-4-[(3,4,5-trimethoxyphenyl)amino]quinazoline-7-carboxylate | Step 5: Hydrolyze the methyl ester (LiOH/NaOH, aq THF/MeOH) to the acid, giving COc1cc(Nc2nc3ccc(C(=O)O)cc3n2CCCNC(=O)OC(C)(C)C)cc(OC)c1OC

